# Commit Title Format

When proposing a git commit title, ALWAYS format it as a single
slash-and-hyphen delimited string: a `Type/` prefix followed by a
kebab-case description. No spaces, no trailing period.

Format:

```
Type/short-kebab-case-description
```

Examples:

```
Fix/set-length-to-fixed-question-count-instead-of-mastered-only
Add/apple-sign-in-support
Update/review-screen-counter-label
```

- Use a capitalized verb prefix (`Fix`, `Add`, `Update`, `Remove`, `Refactor`, etc.).
- Replace every space in the description with a hyphen.
- Keep a longer body/summary as normal prose below the title when useful.
- NEVER commit or push unless the user explicitly instructs it.
